attributes.ACCESSKEY: Sets or retrieves the accelerator key for the object.
attributes.ALIGN: Sets or retrieves how the object is aligned with adjacent text.
attributes.ALT: Sets or retrieves a text alternative to the graphic.
attributes.ATOMICSELECTION: Specifies whether the element and its contents must be selected as a whole, indivisible unit.
attributes.AUTOCOMPLETE: Sets or retrieves the status of AutoComplete for the object.
attributes.BEGIN: Sets or retrieves the delay time before the timeline begins playing on the element.
attributes.BORDER: Sets or retrieves the width of the border to draw around the object.
attributes.CHECKED: Sets or retrieves the state of the check box or radio button.
attributes.CLASS: Sets or retrieves the class of the object.
attributes.COLOR: Sets or retrieves the color to be used by the object.
attributes.CONTENTEDITABLE: Sets or retrieves the string that indicates whether the user can edit the content of the object.
attributes.COORDS: Sets or retrieves the coordinates of the object.
attributes.DATAFLD: Sets or retrieves which field of a given data source, as specified by the dataSrc property, to bind to the specified object.
attributes.DATAFORMATAS: Sets or retrieves how to render the data supplied to the object.
attributes.DATASRC: Sets or retrieves the source of the data for data binding.
attributes.DIR: Sets or retrieves the reading order of the object.
attributes.DISABLED: Sets or retrieves the status of the object.
attributes.DYNSRC: Sets or retrieves the address of a video clip or VRML world to display in the window.
attributes.END: Sets or retrieves a value indicating the end time for the element, or the end of the simple duration when the element is set to repeat.
attributes.FACE: Sets or retrieves the current typeface family.
attributes.GALLERYIMG: Sets or retrieves whether the My Pictures image toolbar is visible for the current image.
attributes.HEIGHT: Sets or retrieves the height of the object.
attributes.HIDEFOCUS: Sets or retrieves the value indicating whether the object visibly indicates that it has focus.
attributes.HREF: Sets or retrieves the destination URL or anchor point.
attributes.HREFLANG: Sets or retrieves the language code of the object.
attributes.HSPACE: Sets or retrieves the horizontal margin for the object.
attributes.ID: Retrieves the string identifying the object.
attributes.ISMAP: Sets or retrieves whether the image is a server-side image map.
attributes.LANG: Sets or retrieves the language to use.
attributes.LANGUAGE: Sets or retrieves the language in which the current script is written.
attributes.LOOP: Sets or retrieves the number of times a sound or video clip will loop when activated.
attributes.LOWSRC: Sets or retrieves a lower resolution image to display.
attributes.MAXLENGTH: Sets or retrieves the maximum number of characters that the user can enter in a text control.
attributes.METHODS: Sets or retrieves the list of HTTP methods supported by the object.
attributes.MULTIPLE: Sets or retrieves the Boolean value indicating whether multiple items can be selected from a list.
attributes.NAME: Sets or retrieves the name of the object.
attributes.NOWRAP: Sets or retrieves whether the browser automatically performs wordwrap.
attributes.READONLY: Sets or retrieves the value indicated whether the content of the object is read-only.
attributes.REL: Sets or retrieves the relationship between the object and the destination of the link.
attributes.REV: Sets or retrieves the relationship between the object and the destination of the link.
attributes.SHAPE: Sets or retrieves the shape of the object.
attributes.SYSTEMCAPTIONS: Indicates whether to display a text equivalent of the audio portion of the presentation.
attributes.SYSTEMOVERDUBORSUBTITLE: Specifies whether overdubs or subtitles render during a presentation.
attributes.SIZE: Sets or retrieves the number of rows in the list box.
attributes.SRC: Sets or retrieves a URL to be loaded by the object.
attributes.START: Sets or retrieves when a video clip file should begin playing.
attributes.SYNCMASTER: Sets or retrieves whether the time container must synchronize playback to this element.
attributes.TABINDEX: Sets or retrieves the index that defines the tab order for the object.
attributes.TARGET: Sets or retrieves the window or frame at which to target content.
attributes.TIMECONTAINER: Sets or retrieves the type of timeline associated with an element.
attributes.TITLE: Sets or retrieves advisory information (a ToolTip) for the object.
attributes.TYPE: Sets or retrieves the MIME type of the object.
attributes.UNSELECTABLE: Specifies that an element cannot be selected.
attributes.URN: Sets or retrieves a URN for a target document.
attributes.USEMAP: Sets or retrieves the URL, often with a bookmark extension (#name), to use as a client-side image map.
attributes.VALUE: Sets or retrieves the value which is returned to the server when the form control is submitted.
attributes.VCARD_NAME: Sets or retrieves the vCard value of the object to use for the AutoComplete box.
attributes.VSPACE: Sets or retrieves the vertical margin for the object.
attributes.WIDTH: Sets or retrieves the calculated width of the object.
attributes.WRAP: Sets or retrieves how to handle wordwrapping in the object.

styles.ACCELERATOR: Sets or retrieves a string that indicates whether the object contains an accelerator key.
styles.background: Sets or retrieves up to five separate background properties of the object.
styles.background-attachment: Sets or retrieves how the background image is attached to the object within the document.
styles.background-color: Sets or retrieves the color behind the content of the object.
styles.background-image: Sets or retrieves the background image of the object.
styles.background-position: Sets or retrieves the position of the background of the object.
styles.background-position-x: Sets or retrieves the x-coordinate of the backgroundPosition property.
styles.background-position-y: Sets or retrieves the y-coordinate of the backgroundPosition property.
styles.background-repeat: Sets or retrieves how the backgroundImage property of the object is tiled.
styles.behavior: Sets or retrieves the location of the Introduction to DHTML Behaviors.
styles.border: Sets or retrieves the properties to draw around the object.
styles.border-bottom: Sets or retrieves the properties of the bottom border of the object.
styles.border-bottom-color: Sets or retrieves the color of the bottom border of the object.
styles.border-bottom-style: Sets or retrieves the style of the bottom border of the object.
styles.border-bottom-width: Sets or retrieves the width of the bottom border of the object.
styles.border-color: Sets or retrieves the border color of the object.
styles.border-left: Sets or retrieves the properties of the left border of the object.
styles.border-left-color: Sets or retrieves the color of the left border of the object.
styles.border-left-style: Sets or retrieves the style of the left border of the object.
styles.border-left-width: Sets or retrieves the width of the left border of the object.
styles.border-right: Sets or retrieves the properties of the right border of the object.
styles.border-right-color: Sets or retrieves the color of the right border of the object.
styles.border-right-style: Sets or retrieves the style of the right border of the object.
styles.border-right-width: Sets or retrieves the width of the right border of the object.
styles.border-style: Sets or retrieves the style of the left, right, top, and bottom borders of the object.
styles.border-top: Sets or retrieves the properties of the top border of the object.
styles.border-top-color: Sets or retrieves the color of the top border of the object.
styles.border-top-style: Sets or retrieves the style of the top border of the object.
styles.border-top-width: Sets or retrieves the width of the top border of the object.
styles.border-width: Sets or retrieves the width of the left, right, top, and bottom borders of the object.
styles.bottom: Sets or retrieves the bottom position of the object in relation to the bottom of the next positioned object in the document hierarchy.
styles.clear: Sets or retrieves whether the object allows floating objects on its left side, right side, or both, so that the next text displays past the floating objects.
styles.clip: Sets or retrieves which part of a positioned object is visible.
styles.color: Sets or retrieves the color of the text of the object.
styles.cursor: Sets or retrieves the type of cursor to display as the mouse pointer moves over the object.
styles.direction: Sets or retrieves the reading order of the object.
styles.display: Sets or retrieves whether the object is rendered.
styles.filter: Sets or retrieves the filter or collection of filters applied to the object.
styles.float: Sets or retrieves on which side of the object the text will flow.
styles.font: Sets or retrieves a combination of separate font properties of the object. Alternatively, sets or retrieves one or more of six user-preference fonts.

styles.font-family: Sets or retrieves the name of the font used for text in the object.
styles.font-size: Sets or retrieves a value that indicates the font size used for text in the object.
styles.font-style: Sets or retrieves the font style of the object as italic, normal, or oblique.
styles.font-variant: Sets or retrieves whether the text of the object is in small capital letters.
styles.font-weight: Sets or retrieves the weight of the font of the object.
styles.height: Sets or retrieves the height of the object.
styles.ime-mode: Sets or retrieves the state of an Input Method Editor (IME).
styles.layout-flow: Sets or retrieves the direction and flow of the content in the object.
styles.layout-grid: Sets or retrieves the composite document grid properties that specify the layout of text characters.
styles.layout-grid-char: Sets or retrieves the size of the character grid used for rendering the text content of an element.
styles.layout-grid-line: Sets or retrieves the gridline value used for rendering the text content of an element.
styles.layout-grid-mode: Sets or retrieves whether the text layout grid uses two dimensions.
styles.layout-grid-type: Sets or retrieves the type of grid used for rendering the text content of an element.
styles.left: Sets or retrieves the position of the object relative to the left edge of the next positioned object in the document hierarchy.
styles.letter-spacing: Sets or retrieves the amount of additional space between letters in the object.
styles.line-break: Sets or retrieves line-breaking rules for Japanese text.
styles.line-height: Sets or retrieves the distance between lines in the object.
styles.margin: Sets or retrieves the width of the top, right, bottom, and left margins of the object.
styles.margin-bottom: Sets or retrieves the height of the bottom margin of the object.
styles.margin-left: Sets or retrieves the width of the left margin of the object.
styles.margin-right: Sets or retrieves the width of the right margin of the object.
styles.margin-top: Sets or retrieves the height of the top margin of the object.
styles.opacity: Sets or retrieves the opacity of the object.
styles.overflow: Sets or retrieves a value indicating how to manage the content of the object when the content exceeds the height or width of the object.
styles.overflow-x: Sets or retrieves how to manage the content of the object when the content exceeds the width of the object.
styles.overflow-y: Sets or retrieves how to manage the content of the object when the content exceeds the height of the object.
styles.padding: Sets or retrieves the amount of space to insert between the object and its margin or, if there is a border, between the object and its border.
styles.padding-bottom: Sets or retrieves the amount of space to insert between the bottom border of the object and the content.
styles.padding-left: Sets or retrieves the amount of space to insert between the left border of the object and the content.
styles.padding-right: Sets or retrieves the amount of space to insert between the right border of the object and the content.
styles.padding-top: Sets or retrieves the amount of space to insert between the top border of the object and the content.
styles.page-break-after: Sets or retrieves a value indicating whether a page break occurs after the object.
styles.page-break-before: Sets or retrieves a string indicating whether a page break occurs before the object.
styles.position: Sets or retrieves the type of positioning used for the object.
styles.right: Sets or retrieves the position of the object relative to the right edge of the next positioned object in the document hierarchy.
styles.scrollbar-3dlight-color: Sets or retrieves the color of the top and left edges of the scroll box and scroll arrows of a scroll bar.
styles.scrollbar-arrow-color: Sets or retrieves the color of the arrow elements of a scroll arrow.
styles.scrollbar-base-color: Sets or retrieves the color of the main elements of a scroll bar, which include the scroll box, track, and scroll arrows.
styles.scrollbar-darkshadow-color: Sets or retrieves the color of the gutter of a scroll bar.
styles.scrollbar-face-color: Sets or retrieves the color of the scroll box and scroll arrows of a scroll bar.
styles.scrollbar-highlight-color: Sets or retrieves the color of the top and left edges of the scroll box and scroll arrows of a scroll bar.
styles.scrollbar-shadow-color: Sets or retrieves the color of the bottom and right edges of the scroll box and scroll arrows of a scroll bar.
styles.scrollbar-track-color: Sets or retrieves the color of the track element of a scroll bar.
styles.text-align: Sets or retrieves whether the text in the object is left-aligned, right-aligned, centered, or justified.
styles.text-align-last: Sets or retrieves how to align the last line or only line of text in the object.
styles.text-autospace: Sets or retrieves the autospacing and narrow space width adjustment of text.
styles.text-decoration: Sets or retrieves a value that indicates whether the text in the object has blink, line-through, overline, or underline decorations.
styles.text-indent: Sets or retrieves the indentation of the first line of text in the object.
styles.text-justify: Sets or retrieves the type of alignment used to justify text in the object.
styles.text-kashida-space: Sets or retrieves the ratio of kashida expansion to white space expansion when justifying lines of text in the object.
styles.text-overflow: Sets or retrieves a value that indicates whether to render ellipses(...) to indicate text overflow.
styles.text-transform: Sets or retrieves the rendering of the text in the object.
styles.text-underline-position: Sets or retrieves the position of the underline decoration that is set through the textDecoration property of the object.
styles.top: Sets or retrieves the position of the object relative to the top of the next positioned object in the document hierarchy.
styles.unicode-bidi: Sets or retrieves the level of embedding with respect to the bidirectional algorithm.

styles.vertical-align: Sets or retrieves the vertical alignment of the object.
styles.visibility: Sets or retrieves whether the content of the object is displayed.
styles.white-space: Sets or retrieves a value that indicates whether lines are automatically broken inside the object.
styles.width: Sets or retrieves the width of the object.
styles.word-break: Sets or retrieves line-breaking behavior within words, particularly where multiple languages appear in the object.
styles.word-spacing: Sets or retrieves the amount of additional space between words in the object.
styles.word-wrap: Sets or retrieves whether to break words when the content exceeds the boundaries of its container.
styles.writing-mode: Sets or retrieves the direction and flow of the content in the object.
styles.z-index: Sets or retrieves the stacking order of positioned objects.
styles.zoom: Sets or retrieves the magnification scale of the object.

events.onabort: Fires when the user aborts the download of an image.
events.onactivate: Fires when the object is set as the active element.
events.onafterupdate: Fires on a databound object after successfully updating the associated data in the data source object.
events.onbeforeactivate: Fires immediately before the object is set as the active element.
events.onbeforecopy: Fires on the source object before the selection is copied to the system clipboard.
events.onbeforecut: Fires on the source object before the selection is deleted from the document.
events.onbeforedeactivate: Fires immediately before the activeElement is changed from the current object to another object in the parent document.
events.onbeforeeditfocus: Fires before an object contained in an editable element enters a UI-activated state or when an editable container object is control selected.
events.onbeforepaste: Fires on the target object before the selection is pasted from the system clipboard to the document.
events.onbeforeupdate: Fires on a databound object before updating the associated data in the data source object.
events.onblur: Fires when the object loses the input focus.
events.onchange: Fires when the contents of the object or selection have changed.
events.onclick: Fires when the user clicks the left mouse button on the object.
events.oncontextmenu: Fires when the user clicks the right mouse button in the client area, opening the context menu.
events.oncontrolselect: Fires when the user is about to make a control selection of the object.
events.oncopy: Fires on the source element when the user copies the object or selection, adding it to the system clipboard.
events.oncut: Fires on the source element when the object or selection is removed from the document and added to the system clipboard.
events.ondblclick: Fires when the user double-clicks the object.
events.ondeactivate: Fires when the activeElement is changed from the current object to another object in the parent document.
events.ondrag: Fires on the source object continuously during a drag operation.
events.ondragend: Fires on the source object when the user releases the mouse at the close of a drag operation.
events.ondragenter: Fires on the target element when the user drags the object to a valid drop target.
events.ondragleave: Fires on the target object when the user moves the mouse out of a valid drop target during a drag operation.
events.ondragover: Fires on the target element continuously while the user drags the object over a valid drop target.
events.ondragstart: Fires on the source object when the user starts to drag a text selection or selected object.
events.ondrop: Fires on the target object when the mouse button is released during a drag-and-drop operation.
events.onerror: Fires when an error occurs during object loading.
events.onerrorupdate: Fires on a databound object when an error occurs while updating the associated data in the data source object.
events.onfilterchange: Fires when a visual filter changes state or completes a transition.
events.onfocus: Fires when the object receives focus.
events.onfocusin: Fires for an element just prior to setting focus on that element.
events.onfocusout: Fires for the current element with focus immediately after moving focus to another element.
events.onhelp: Fires when the user presses the F1 key while the browser is the active window.
events.onkeydown: Fires when the user presses a key.
events.onkeypress: Fires when the user presses an alphanumeric key.
events.onkeyup: Fires when the user releases a key.
events.onlayoutcomplete: Fires when the print or print preview layout process finishes filling the current LayoutRect object with content from the source document.
events.onload: Fires immediately after the browser loads the object.
events.onlosecapture: Fires when the object loses the mouse capture.
events.onmousedown: Fires when the user clicks the object with either mouse button.
events.onmouseenter: Fires when the user moves the mouse pointer into the object.
events.onmouseleave: Fires when the user moves the mouse pointer outside the boundaries of the object.
events.onmousemove: Fires when the user moves the mouse over the object.
events.onmouseout: Fires when the user moves the mouse pointer outside the boundaries of the object.
events.onmouseover: Fires when the user moves the mouse pointer into the object.
events.onmouseup: Fires when the user releases a mouse button while the mouse is over the object.
events.onmousewheel: Fires when the wheel button is rotated.
events.onmoveend: Fires when the object stops moving.
events.onmovestart: Fires when the object starts to move.
events.onpaste: Fires on the target object when the user pastes data, transferring the data from the system clipboard to the document.
events.onpropertychange: Fires when a property changes on the object.
events.onreadystatechange: Fires when the state of the object has changed.
events.onresize: Fires when the size of the object is about to change.
events.onresizeend: Fires when the user finishes changing the dimensions of the object in a control selection.
events.onresizestart: Fires when the user begins to change the dimensions of the object in a control selection.
events.onscroll: Fires when the user repositions the scroll box in the scroll bar on the object.
events.onselect: Fires when the current selection changes.
events.onselectstart: Fires when the object is being selected.
events.ontimeerror: Fires whenever a time-specific error occurs, usually as a result of setting a property to an invalid value.
